onsidering test class structure**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about possibly avoiding the helper file by using a public static nested class in my test. I noticed that while the actual class name contains a dollar sign ($), the file or test names don’t. The rules say to never use $ in test class names, but the nested public static class should be accessible. I’ll rename it to `JDBCSQLXMLTest`, making it a standard public class that holds a nested class extending `StAXResult`.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Inspecting nested class access**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering that all top-level classes need to be public, but since this is a nested class, it doesn't fall into that category. JUnit ignores nested classes unless they're marked with @Nested, which is good to know. However, for dynamic access, it seems like I might need some reachability metadata for the nested class constructor. I’m also thinking that the agent conditional should include user code, particularly filtering the org_hsqldb, so I need to dig into that a bit more.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_JZgyBSKghBaVscZwOGJQXJiY|fc_05ea79250a80ec6e0169f61d5240cc819087ea0e5e7da4f6bd\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/user-code-filter.json\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2193, \"output\": 825, \"cacheRead\": 27136, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 30154, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777737026569, \"responseId\": \"resp_05ea79250a80ec6e0169f61d430ca48190b3fbd1e706d39d5f\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.hsqldb:hsqldb:2.4.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-52-31-091353Z.log:2193:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Reviewing XML compilation