sidering file structure and testing**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about the one-to-one mapping between report classes and generated test class files. If each active class has its own dedicated test file, I wonder if a helper file counts as a test class. It seems it’s just a class file, which could be allowed, but maybe not. \\\\n\\\\nI lean towards keeping it nested for simplicity, but I should check if running just the compile is okay, especially since there was an error. The instructions say not to compile or run tests myself, so I need to keep that in mind. Should I add @SuppressWarnings? Also, I might need to search for existing helper classes.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_PMWxzG9j1XAM4kKwrvIAE6vq|fc_05ea79250a80ec6e0169f61ec3a83481908362e122c543f284\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find tests/src -path '*/src/test/java/*Test.java' -type f | head -20 | xargs rg -n \\\"class .* extends|public static class\\\" | head -50\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1159, \"output\": 1226, \"cacheRead\": 56320, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 58705, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777737392038, \"responseId\": \"resp_05ea79250a80ec6e0169f61eb0a42c8190b3978b05692e2cfa\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.hsqldb:hsqldb:2.4.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T15-52-31-091353Z.log:4813:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Inspecting test coverage**\\n\\nI'm wondering if metadata can be applied to an arbitrary test class. It seems likely that a Native Image could fail in certain cases. I should check if earlier tests failed only with the JVM before considering Native tests, but there’s no data available on that. It might be better to focus on `createStAXResult` to 